<span id="freeTextContainer15716135472027260207">I love just about all the books this guy has ever written. His characters are quirky and colorful, his plots always a bit offbeat. And this story of a small-time hood trying to break into the movie business as a producer is no exception. <br/><br/>Elmore leonard is considered a crime writer, yet his characters are rarely (if ever) detectives, policemen, or private eyes. Now that&apos;s a challenge! He is definitely a one-of-a-kind author.<br/>It&apos;s no wonder that Hollywood has made so many movies out of his books!</span>
  <span id="freeText15716135472027260207" style="display:none">I love just about all the books this guy has ever written. His characters are quirky and colorful, his plots always a bit offbeat. And this story of a small-time hood trying to break into the movie business as a producer is no exception. <br /><br />Elmore leonard is considered a crime writer, yet his characters are rarely (if ever) detectives, policemen, or private eyes. Now that's a challenge! He is definitely a one-of-a-kind author.<br />It's no wonder that Hollywood has made so many movies out of his books!</span>
