<div id="review_2529470273" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2529470273" />
    <a title="Bruce" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6821524-bruce"><img alt="Bruce" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1319938296p2/6821524.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2529470273?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bruce" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bruce" href="/user/show/6821524-bruce">Bruce</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385301411" href="/book/show/985029.Get_Shorty">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2529470273" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3233377902581527180">Elmore Leonard has the reputation of being a good writer of crime fiction, but this one may not be one of those. The setting, Hollywood, and the plot, small time loan sharks and enforcers who suddenly are channeling their movie producer alter egos, never took flight for me. Too much sappy dialogue, characters not all that interesting. I wanted to say &quot;CUT. Let&apos;s try it again.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText3233377902581527180" style="display:none">Elmore Leonard has the reputation of being a good writer of crime fiction, but this one may not be one of those. The setting, Hollywood, and the plot, small time loan sharks and enforcers who suddenly are channeling their movie producer alter egos, never took flight for me. Too much sappy dialogue, characters not all that interesting. I wanted to say "CUT. Let's try it again."</span>
  <a data-text-id="3233377902581527180" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
