        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2489751483" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5122543320723215135">Okay wow, that was a slim read. Three days. Faster, even, if it weren’t for work and sleep. Probably a day.<br/><br/>This was fun. Typical crime caper tropes with the characters all being somehow conveniently tied together. Even the Leonard trope where some dude gets shot outta nowhere by the bad guy at the half time mark. Saw this LaBrava too. But the meta-fiction stuff was pretty cool, and never treated like something pretentious to gloat about. It was part of the story, y’know. Like it was good enough </span>
  <span id="freeText5122543320723215135" style="display:none">Okay wow, that was a slim read. Three days. Faster, even, if it weren’t for work and sleep. Probably a day.<br /><br />This was fun. Typical crime caper tropes with the characters all being somehow conveniently tied together. Even the Leonard trope where some dude gets shot outta nowhere by the bad guy at the half time mark. Saw this LaBrava too. But the meta-fiction stuff was pretty cool, and never treated like something pretentious to gloat about. It was part of the story, y’know. Like it was good enough for you to be intrigued about it but not so good that when we focused on the real story i would be missing the little fake story. Bo Callett has to be one of my favorites. Michael Weir was another great character. Great stuff elmore.<br /><br />Still like Mr.Majestik better. That’s at my number one right now.<br /><br />And the ending for this book-hilarious.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5122543320723215135" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

